reviews.text: The service was great. The holiday vibe was nice. The food was good. I'd happily go here again. About as nice of an experience as someone can have at IHOP.

The best IHop experience in the dmv, our server Joan J. was great and very attentive. Spent roughly an hour to an hour and a half. We came in on Sunday afternoon and were seated quickly (no wait time at all!) although you could tell the restaurant was very busy the food came fairly quickly all cooked perfectly served with beverages right away. I noticed as soon as a party leaves the table is quickly cleared and cleaned off which I appreciate.
The place wasn't that clean. The service was slow but staff was friendly. The food was  good however we have eaten better food at other clean IHOP locations.
Server Jason was great and very attentive to us food was on point and came out fast even with a mishap it was corrected and we moved on professionally...
Basically ok, nothing horrible, but nothing special.  And not cheap.  Waffle House is a better deal every time.

I was on travel for a funeral and did a local search for a restaraunt near me. It returned this subway location within a few miles so I gave it a try. This location is attached to an office building but it was accessible from the outside of the building with no extra security measures to have to access the restaraunt, and it was open to the general public. It is a small location with a very small lobby but I would assume they do more carryout business so it was just fine. The sandwich artists were cordial and the food was normal Subway quality. I would return to this location if in the immediate area again on travel.

Food is good, service is good.
Recently renovated and clean.
5 minutes from the UA Mechanical Trade school and UPS.

I must say this location is phenomenal! I usually order here for lunches at my job site. The manager is very kind and professional, and so are the workers. They even called me to make sure that my order was fine after the fact. I have no doubts about the quality of the food when eating here. I would highly recommend eating here!

I visited this subway with the intention of getting lunch and left completely confused. I came in and watched what I presume to be the owner bothering the sandwich maker while they were making my food. I didn’t understand why it was necessary to be yelling at her as well as the other young man. The experience was hard to watch I could see the frustration on both the workers faces. I was satisfied with my food but will not be supporting this Subway anymore.
Service is always slow even with online orders.

Worst experience at a fast food place and ANY BOJANGLES ACROSS THE U.S. I went here and ordered a 3piece meal and also tenders with dirty rice. My friends chicken had been cooked in old oil (pic doesn't do it justice) it was black and tasted like oil. My tenders were cold and rubbery. To make matters worse I opened the dirty rice and to my surprise not only did it smell burnt it tasted burnt. I went inside and the employees gave me some excuse about how the manager was gone and they didn't swap the oil out. I asked for a refund so he went to process it and then ended up charging me a 2nd time for MORE than what my meal was worth. I was told the receipt machine didn't work so no proof could be given. I don't live in the area so I've tried calling for 2 weeks now and the phone is disconnected (what kind of establishment are you people running so unprofessionally?) Ive called corporate and they said I had to file a complaint online which I did but still have not heard back. This is a dirty and disgusting location and should honestly be shut down or have new management. I'm sure they don't wash their hands often in here. I will not stand by and be double charged for the worst food service I've ever experienced in life especially since I have food service in my work history. Id give 0 stars if I could.

Food is ALWAYS good but this location seemed SUPER sketchy.
Young kids hanging out in the lobby & a homeless guy was sleeping on one of the tables, didn't even get greeted when we first walked in, bathrooms were disgusting, it was SUPER hot inside too & I felt on edge the entire time.
Definitely go through the drive-thru if you go here.

I always desire to go here when I go to Virginia and was thrilled 😁 to find there was Bojangles as close as Maryland!!! The biscuits are good if you're a sweets person and I tried the sweet potato 🍠 pie 🥧 for the first time too.

Great breakfast. A little understaffed, so don't be upset if there's a little wait time.

The sausage/egg/cheese biscuits are very tasty.  It tastes like the eggs are prepared on the spot since they're cooked & folded to fit the biscuit. Definitely no "mcdonald-style egg-pucks" here!

Never had the chicken before, but picked it up for a coworker several times and he loves it, asking me to bring him some at least once a month!

Horrible experience. I waited at the drive thru approximately 30 minutes with 2 vehicles in front of me. So no way to leave. When I did pull up I waited another 15 minutes for the cashier. Finally shows up and ask what I ordered. I was going to leave but it’s not a work day and had a taste for their biscuits. Once I received my order I pull away around the corner looked at my food and the biscuit fell a part and food was cold. I pulled around went in the store and showed it to them and the cashier said they were short on help. They were taking orders and also fixing food. He had on gloves put I wasn’t sure if he changed them so I trashed the food when I got to my car. I didn’t get a receipt when I pulled away so I didn’t ask for a refund. I’ll just never go there again.

name: Subway
vicinity: 8445 Annapolis Road Store 8445 D, New Carrollton

reviews.text:
Please be warned that this subway lacks respect for its customer base!

Specifically, an employee knowingly used a derogatory term to my husband after a debate ensued  about a the subway app. This restaurant appears to have financial trouble, has poor management, and terrible customer service. The employee wasted unpurchased food and jeopardized their business’s over a coupon.

We will be making a formal complaint about and obviously never patronizing this location again.

Sign of the time!

I enter and ask to use the bathroom. The worker Altaf allowed me to use the bathroom before purchasing anything. I thought that was pretty nice of him. The vibe was not as warm because of the lack of contentment from the employee. Maybe having a bad day or something. Place was clean and food was good. They have sugar cookies and XXX vitamin water as the fountain drink. I have not seen vitamin water as a fountain drink. That was a treat.

Food was fine, but for some reason it seemed like the staff here didn't know what they were doing. Placed an order 25 minutes in advance and they didn't have it ready, and they seemed somewhat confused about what's going on.
A good subway and very spacious. They have a lot of dine in seating. Customer service is good.

very unpleasant lady was rude and unaccomadative to our vegetarian need tried to drop meat in our food she seemed to fine when dealing with Spanish speaking customers only went because other place was closed food wasn't that good vibe seemed off frm start wouldn't go again
Tell the driver to take it easy on the breaks. It was delivered just like this. Taste is good though.

Called in pizza order on 11/12/22. Gave instructions for driver to call when in drive way. No call. Happen to see tail lights in driveway and headed to door but before I got there, driver rang doorbell and placed pizza on ground in front of door. I informed driver it's unacceptable to place food on ground like that, those were not my instructions. He showed instructions on his phone "leave at door." Called, complained to manager who stated there was no record of my order, I must have called another store. Wrong -- same number previously used, saved in phone. No complaint with pizza. May try another store before totalling saying good-bye to Papa Johns.
Thank you to this location staff and manager that helped with my order and made sure we got it on time! The pizzas were great! I truly appreciate all your help!
I ordered a pizza from here over a hour ago, and it said it delivered and it never came. They are stealing money. Very unprofessional.

My pizza was practically burnt I called the store spoke to the manager to fix it. He could essentially care less I was shocked. I rather drive further to the fairway or lake arbor location than give my money away to this location.

name: Taqueria 3 Reyes
vicinity: 8500 Annapolis Road Unit D, New Carrollton

reviews.text: The food at the taqueria is very good and it's usually served quickly. There is a lot of variety in the choice of meals and beverages. Not all of the staff speaks English, but you can easily easily order what you want by pointing to it in the menu. The place is very clean and comfortable.

Found a hair in my food and when I called asking to speak to a manger I was just left on hold. No effort was give to correct the issue,I’m very dissatisfied with service and professionalism of the management there.

This is the 2nd time I have placed an order over the phone and 1:30hrs later my food still isn’t ready!? Then after paying for 4 tostada ( yea I know right waiting 1:30hrs for 4 tostada is ridiculous) THEY FORGOT 1. I’m sorry but either you guys do not check the orders or don’t know how to count. Their customer service is TERRIBLE!!! They don’t care how long you wait or if they mess up on your order. I’ve learned my lesson to never go here again! Honestly, if you guys don’t know how to take phone order or take them and forget to put them in JUST STOP TALKING PHONE ORDERS!! It will save your business ALOT of frustrated and angry customers.

This place is horrible waited
40 minutes for a torta Mexicana, and when they gave it to me it looked horrible , didnt bring anything it was supposed to bring they only added ham with 1 small piece of avocado disappointing. Workers are rude wouldn’t recommend !

Best quesadilla carne asada! Come hungry, they're huge and mouth watering delicious.

Tacos were also excellent! Had them with a melon drink.. couldn't be better!

This place if I can give it a 0 I would, first off the pizza came warm then on top of that it was not what we ordered. One was a cheese pizza and the other was sausage, (we ordered combo toppings with garlic sauce they didn’t even bring that) then we tried to call them back and and they didn’t not pick up when my sister called it was “busy” and when I called it didn’t even ring. And this is not the first time it happened and the employees are RUDE especially over the phone. DO NOT WAIST YOUR MONEY HERE. Tomorrow my sister is calling corporate and reporting them cuz its to late tonight and this pore service has been happening to many times. (NOT WHAT WE ORDERED) we ended up throwing it away it ruined our grate night we had.
Ordered a pepperoni pizza and salad yesterday. It was hot and enjoyable! Took exactly 15 min to be ready as the employee stated. Good spot for a hot pizza.

I ordered carryout on Saturday January 21st.  Believe my order was 654.  When I called my order in, the person taking it was extremely professional.   I ordered 2 pizza's.   My complete order was read back to me.  Upon arrival at the Restaurant,  my order was ready and cooked to perfection.   I truly liked everyone involved in my Pizza order.  Please thank your staff for a job well done, and I look forward to my next visit to Domino's.

So I order buffalo wings and they brought me this which I don’t even know what that is. I called back and they never answered they said it was ringing but it didn’t and then my delivery person Abdul maljeet didn’t deliver the food to my door he made us go to the front of the house where my cars was parked he also took a while to hand me the food and made me wait a long time

My online delivery order was placed at 8:16pm February 24th, 2023 and my estimated delivery time was 50mins. At 9:03pm I received a text saying that my delivery driver "Brandi'' was on the way. Brandi never showed up. I called the store multiple times; NO ANSWER! At 10:30pm I received another text saying that my delivery driver "Abdul" was on the way with my order. Again, Abdul never showed up. At around 10:45pm I got a call from the store apologizing and asking me if I still wanted the order or if I wanted a refund, and because the order was for my child I said yes to still wanting the delivery. It's now 11:42pm and I am just receiving my order literally 2 minutes ago. I WILL BE CALLIING CUSTOMER SEEVICE ON THE MORNING! BEYOND RIDICULOUS! 😡
It is an amazing place to eat

plus_code.compound_code: W4RJ+V3 Landover, Greater Landover, MD, USA

reviews.text: Ardmore Carry Out catered our annual Maryland Day Catholic Terps pig roast and it was amazing! First they were able to help us on short notice when our previous vendor was unable, then they brought us the most delicious pork, chicken and sides we could have ever asked for! Spectacular - and the best part was the leftovers.... which there are now none!!! Thank you George and team - amazing food!!!
Very friendly and very accommodating. The food is delicious and nice size portions. Everything is delicious.

I needed food last minute for a company event. I spoke with George the day before, and he was able to have food ready for us with less than a 24 hours notice. He saved our company lunch. Not only was he able to complete my order but the food was amazing. Everyone in my office loved it! We will be ordering again!
Thank you George for your amazing customer service!
The breakfast already be made so it’s not hot they never answer their phone and they occasionally gets the order wrong
Great breakfast and lunch spot. Friendly staff and amazing food

The food is absolutely DELICIOUS 😋!  First visit. Entree + 2 sides = $20.99. I ordered salmon, fried rice, veggies and 2 cornbreads. I ordered at 6:25pm and my number was called to pick choices at 6:40pm. One of the other guests mentioned that I actually came at one of the busiest times so obviously she was a regular to know this. I decided to eat in. The place was very busy with people coming in and out but actually very clean. The tables were clean and so was the floor. Plenty of food choices (all kinds of fish, meatloaf, pork ribs, pork chops, chicken, turkey wings, all kinds of starch and veggies). and parking spaces. The food was nicely flavored and a great portion size (see pic). I will definitely revisit to try other items on the menu

Excellent food, generous portions. We ordered baked salmon, catfish, shrimp and oysters with plenty of sides to go around. The food was cooked well, not fried too hard, and the salmon was not dry at all. Impressed, we will be back.

I  can't get enough of this place. I drive about 40 min to get to Mid Atlantic Seafood. The food is always fresh and so much to choose from. You can eat there every day of the month and never eat the same thing. Let me tell you the portions are fantastic. I have never been able to eat all the food in one sitting. Defiantly worth the money.

The food is usual descent but the last tome I ate here the greens and yams were bland no flavor at all. The ribs are good tender and meaty. I wonder if they changed cooks because the yams especially were missing something like vanilla extract, cinnamon, but meg etc. It would be nice to have some representation in the staff considering the soul food they are serving. But it is what it is.
Well, it was a good run. I always knew this place wasn't the cleanest but you get some of the best food from a hole in the wall spot... Today I found a dead ROACH in my fried rice. 🤢🤢

Horrible customer service today. I walked in there first and no one was in the line And no one asked me if I wanted to place an order or anything. They were all just talking behind the counter. And then a man and his son walked in behind me. Then the employees started asking the man and his son if they wanted to place an order And I let this go because I was wanting to be nice. And then one of the employees came up to me and said that I need to go around as if I had cut the line. I told him that I was waiting there first and he told me that I was standing in the wrong place (in front of the cheese slicer) and that I would have to go around and that this was wrong. Absolutely horrible customer service. They made a big assumption that had cut the line and gave me no benefit of the doubt when really if they had just paid attention from the beginning instead of ignoring me behind the counter the whole time but they would have seen that I had gotten there first. I will not be returning to this location
Better than my local Jersey Mike's. You can actually see your Philly cheese steak being made,not like the one in my area 27106, where they make it in the back.

Very good store to get subs made. Always fresh and "packed" !!😃
I wouldn't hesitate to come back or refer them to others. The Annapolis Rd. Jersey Mike's are worth checking out !!
I usually just write positive reviews to recommend good establishments. This Jersey Mike's is staffed with really kind hard working folks. I would recommend it 100%.

This place is not for me. I know A LOT of people who like the sandwiches here but I just prefer something else. Staff was friendly and cared when I said it was my first time. They let me take my time and made suggestions without irritation. Even as I am writing this I have raised the stars from 2 to 4. I thought food was just okay but you may not. Please try it for yourself.

Came here to get a bite for lunch and i was satisfied with the overall experience. It was a clean atmosphere for the most part and a kind staff. I was in the store for 20 mins from walking in to walking out with what i want. The line was long but was steady moving and the mobile orders were coming in hot. I understand the wait but still got the food i wanted in a reasonable time and reasonable fashion. Mask are still required supposedly but its not for long hopefully 🙏🏾.

I love chipotle very much, but this was probably my first time having an issue like this in a while. My mom went to go get food from this location and then I found something that was unknown in my food. Looked like mold which I ended up not eating the bowl. Luckily my mother was able to get another bowl along with chips and salsa for free.

Like with most Chipotle's how much food you get depends on the server. Most days it's pretty good portions. Last time it was smaller then the usual. Standard chipotle food quality. Restaurant is a bit small

I had my doubts just because if the location but my in law gturned me on to this one, line moves fast, clean serves a good portion of food regardless of who you are, friendly staff, very hard working young ones.

I love everything about this place. Donna & Jessica are the friendliest ladies I've met. Donna especially makes me look forward to my meals. Patient & all smiles.  Very healthy & fresh stuff. They deserve 10 stars 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟 🌟

The service was faster than most African restaurants I have been to. Ordered over $70 in food and it was all ready in 20 mins!! Then went next door to sit down because this part opens up at 11 a.m
The decor was great and the the service there too was friendly and professional.
All the food was delicious 😋 will definitely return. 10/10 will recommend 👌🏽

This was my 2nd time visiting this wonderful wonderful place. Never has traditional African food before and  I’ve been wanting to try it. I’m glad my 1st experience was here! I explained to the staff it was my 1st time and they were very patient and helpful. The food was excellent, the service was excellent, clean bright environment and the prices are reasonable.. If you’re looking for authentic African food, look no further.

Great Nigerian restaurant.

I was seated immediately when I entered.  The service was fast until a large party came in but the wait wasn't too long.

The jollof rice was excellent. Great flavor and portion size was really good.  The baked chicken was very good and flavorful as well.

When I left,, I noticed a few doors down a carryout of the same restaurant.

I had a very enjoyable meal at Jolloff Etcetera. I ordered Amala, ewedu and gbegiri with assorted meat. It was absolutely yum!!!
First time here and I shall definitively return.
I recommend if you have a taste for authentic Nigerian cuisine.

By the way, I love the vintage car representing the Nigerian flag colors parked right in front of the restaurant. That’s so cool.

Good Service ✅
🚻Restroom
Courteous Staff✅
Lovely Ambiance ✅
🚻Restroom✅

First time trying to fufu and egusi with goat so I don’t really have a reference on what it should taste like but everything was good. Easy to find, the employees were nice and even a random customer was saying it was the best within a 15 mile radius.

name: Starbucks
vicinity: Shopping Center, 8498 Annapolis Road Carrollton, New Carrollton

reviews.text: Nice Starbucks.  Clean as airy inside, plenty of great seating —tables and conversation areas, and typical Starbucks drink and food selections.  Easy on/off drive-through, and polite and friendly workers.  Tons of parking lot parking.

I usually have a pleasant experience ordering from Starbucks and never complain, even if my order is wrong.  At this location it was otherwise. The lady who took my order seemed fine at first but then caught an attitude when I asked for 3 shots of espresso for the venti drink instead of 2…I handed her my reusable cup and she attempted to scan the bottom but this was a generic cup. Another staff member came behind her (with attitude) stated the cup wasn’t from Starbucks and asked me (very rudely) to take off the top/straw. I stated, “they were funny here (at that location)” because I do not tolerate any attitude when it comes to me being polite. I hate to add a bad review but people need to work on their tone and attitudes. Lastly, my drink was supposed to be cold and it was warm. Thank you!

Most inefficient Starbucks I've been to. Yesterday they were out of cold; however, thankfully had a decent substitute salted caramel latte. Today they were out of heavy whipping cream. So I ordered a latte again. What I got was milk with a hint of coffee. Who ever worked yesterday thank you!, but please help share your knowledge with today's crew.

We were passing through on our way back to NJ and decided to stop here. They made our drinks quickly even though they were busy. When my daughters drink didn’t come out right a nice barista David offered to remake it and it turned out perfectly. I got a hot oat milk latte and it tasted “burnt”. Why i only have 4 stars. They are new - maybe still learning here.
It's a hit-or-miss place most of the time. In most cases, the drive through moves at a painful crawl so it's better to either order online and pick up inside or just walk-in to place your order.

I don't do Dunkin ever. When I come down this area, that's all there is. This is the only one I come to. Strange right? This spot is very welcoming and on the ball taking care of that drive thru. I usually walk in because it's empty. Anywho. Love this spot.

I was okay with not getting a good morning returned to me each time I greeted the employees, but to mess up multiple times with my order was a bit frustrating and disappointing. I swiped my loyalty ID to get the $3 cold brew and was told “No” and that “the regular price for cold brew is $3.59…” regardless of the special ran and the cheaper price I showed via my app. Not only did I end up not saving $2+ but I got shorted on my change due and requested the remaining amount (still was incorrect), didn’t receive a straw (went back for it and actually got a goodbye greeting after my 3rd/last request for something), and my medium cold brew didn’t even have the standard 3 shots/swirls of flavor added when requesting a medium (I received 1 each but didn’t realize this until reaching home and tasting my drink and reading the label on the cup). 😫

Lately since I’ve been going to this Dunkin’ Donuts my orders have always been messed up it was never like this in the past and I’ve been come to this Dunkin’ Donuts for eight years today I ordered a cinnamon bagel with cream cheese and butter I got a cinnamon bagel with butter  and it’s not even toasted last time I order food I got the total opposite of what I asked for I think I’m gonna gave this Dunkin’ Donuts a break for a while

The line stretched into the highway and we waiting in line for 3min. Placed an order for 2 hazelnut iced coffee one with almond milk. When we got them the almond milk drink had a note of 3 shots of sugar(we didn't ask for) and asked that it be fixed. The lady at the window was obviously new and should've been assigned something with less detail until she learns the ropes. I watched her ask another employee something concerning the check and by the look on her face she was getting blown off. She gave a the drink with more almond milk but it was still awful. Ended up going to Wendy's for a frostychino..... more money spent
They were very quick and there were a lot of customers to take care of. Kudos for the hard working crew there! My breakfast was delicious 😋

We were so hungry and looking for a breakfast spot to go to before we hit the road back home. we stopped at another spot but they did not have social distance and when I called this place and asked if they had social distinct seating, they did. I think most people forget that we are still in a pandemic and distancing yourself from others is important. I was happy to see that not only were the seating spaced out, but the food was served in complete plastic containers plastic spoons plastic forks plastic cups. No server you order your food and you sit down. I would definitely go here again. The food was delicious the price was right and the place made me feel safe about eating out.

The outside appearance made me hesitant but once we entered you could tell it was a popular local spot. The staff were pleasant and the food was pretty good. Portion sizes were good. Would definitely eat here again.
Loved this place!!! Highly recommend.  Food was awesome. Could not have made it better myself.  Staff very friendly and helpful! Was just passing through but will make sure to stop in again!

Just passing through, googled breakfast places near by. Don't judge a book by its covers, the outside could use some love but the food is amazing . Try the omlette!! If I lived in MD this would be a staple breakfast place. And the staff is great too!

OMG!!! Ever since the pandemic this place is a shell of itself!!! The menu is about 1/4 of what it used to be. No more waitress. You buy / grab "YOU" clean a table and sit down and they will DROP your carryout style food to you. I used to SWEAR by this place. They need to change the name because this place is NOT the Pancake House I've been going to for over 20 years!!!
Food is consistently quality however the straw situation needs to be revisited by management. Super thin straw material makes it hard to drink. Thanks

Visited Bell in Landover Hills, Md on 9/11/22 around 9:30 pm.  Usually visits the Bell in Colmar Manor, Md but closed for 6 weeks for remodeling.  Anyway, the Landover Hills one was surprisingly good, tasty!  Food was hot and fresh.  We ate in the car and enjoyed it.  Our order was perfect and our drink was cold. 3 people ordered.  Will visit again!

One of the best taco bell locations I've been to. The amount of taco meat used is the secret to a good taco bell experience - even their basic hard shell taco is great. I recommend their crunchwrap supreme because the distribution of ingredients is better than I've had at most locations.

Been here numerous times and the quality is pretty good for Taco Bell. I've had no issues with bad food. Sometimes I get the common-mistake fast food places have where the order isn't made correctly, but that's like 1 out of 30 visits.

Sometimes they've requested I do weird things, like back-up in the drive-thru so I don't trip their motion-sensors for cars, since their Headquarters tracks time vehicles spend in queue, but I think that's an issue their HQ should just stop tracking entirely. I'd rather sit and wait for my food to be made HOT, safe, and correct instead of hasty and potentially unhealthy.

I used the drive thru and the food was hot when given to me and also when I got home. They allowed me to check my bag before I pulled off because I got a lot of food. The workers were really nice and pleasant and the food was really good too

Super long wait for drive-thru, sometimes 8 cars long (But don't fault them. It's important your food be HOT and prepared properly, not hasty and a health risk).

Quality is normally okay, but the last time I went a few months back, my housemate said the fries tasted the way dead mouse smells (long story, lol). We threw the food out and luckily didn't get food poisoning.

Nice selections, clean restaurant,  nice employee but cold food....  could not eat it and just did not take it back for fear of retaliation.  Got the Italian chicken and thr fried mozzarella was cold..fries cold this was early in the morning like 11:20 am should not have been like that. So disappointing. I don't eat out often but this is one reason why. I tried to put the food in the air fryer when I got home but it just wasn't good.
Super nice folks!  Good food, quick and polite service, and generous with extras.  Glad we stopped here!
Extremely clean! The burger wasn't as hot as I expected for being called "fresh" but overall, I would recommend it.
Unfortunately I didn't realize they ripped me off until I got home. I ordered a Dave's Double, I paid for a Dave's Double, and they gave me a Double Stack (i.e. junior patties and no lettuce).

This store CONSTANTLY has customers wrapped around the dining area in a single line but with multiple cashiers available....ENOUGH!! Store managers FIX THIS ISSUE PLEASE! It's been going on for WAAAAY Too long!

If there was a no star  option,  definitely  would be that!!
How do you close before you close and don't have what the customer wants, like French fries would  for example which does not take long to fry at all, again especially  before you close! Chicken was cold, sides were cold, money in the trash literally!!! WORST  popeyes in maryland!!! Never will I EVER  recommend this place!
FYI teach your employees more than " can I help you" with a fake smile!
Worst customer service  experience we have ever had!

I am going to stop patronizing this location.  I am so tired of hobos lurking around the front door with no mask on approaching people.  With all of the carjacking, drugs, and assortment of other thievery going on this place is not safe. Management does nothing to make the loiters move away from the door or off of the premises.

First time trying Popeyes, i wanted the ghost pepper wings but they were not available.
They were kind enough to give me spicy wings.
They had a nice crunch and were flavourful.

I ordered on the app ~10-15min prior to walking in and when i came in, the cashier was a little rude and ignoring me. When I finally did get her attention (by standing in front of the register for several min after waiting in line), I said I wanted to check if a mobile order was ready, to which she immediately said "no, its not ready yet" without even looking at anything or asking for any of my information. 5 min later a much more helpful employee assisted me and grabbed it off the shelf where it had been sitting the entire time. Won't be back.

Also - got the fabled chicken sandwich for the first time (normally go spicy bone-in chicken) - it wasn't even that good y'all! Def going back to the classic stuff next time (at a different location!)
